{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H9o1mN4K5jkqDyrzekzaMz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16.4: Update Validation ACs and Runner for New Tiers\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→Status: ready-for-dev\n     5→\n     6→## Story\n     7→\n     8→As a codeharness developer,\n     9→I want the validation AC registry and runner to use the new `VerificationTier` vocabulary,\n    10→So that the self-validation system classifies and dispatches ACs using the unified tier system.\n    11→\n    12→## Acceptance Criteria\n    13→\n    14→- [ ] AC1: Given `validation-acs.ts`, when `getTestProvableACs()` is called, then it returns all ACs with `verificationMethod === 'cli'` (same data as old `getCliVerifiableACs()`), and the old function name still works as a deprecated alias <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC2: Given `validation-acs.ts`, when `getEnvironmentProvableACs()` is called, then it returns all ACs with `verificationMethod === 'integration'` (same data as old `getIntegrationRequiredACs()`), and the old function name still works as a deprecated alias <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC3: Given `validation-runner.ts` `executeValidationAC()`, when an AC with `verificationMethod === 'integration'` is passed, then it returns `blocked` with reason `'integration-required'` (no behavioral change, but a JSDoc comment explains the mapping to `environment-provable` tier) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC4: Given `validation-runner-types.ts`, when inspected, then all comments referencing old tier names (`cli-verifiable`, `integration-required`) are updated to reference new tier names (`test-provable`, `environment-provable`), and `reason: 'integration-required'` string is kept with a comment noting it's a status reason, not a tier name <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC5: Given `validation-ac-types.ts`, when `VerificationMethod` type is inspected, then it has a JSDoc comment noting correspondence: `'cli'` maps to `test-provable` tier, `'integration'` maps to `environment-provable` tier <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→\n    20→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    21→\n    22→- [ ] Task 1: Rename helpers in `validation-acs.ts` (AC: 1, 2)\n    23→  - [ ] 1.1: Create `getTestProvableACs()` — filters `verificationMethod === 'cli'`\n    24→  - [ ] 1.2: Create `getEnvironmentProvableACs()` — filters `verificationMethod === 'integration'`\n    25→  - [ ] 1.3: Keep `getCliVerifiableACs()` as deprecated alias calling `getTestProvableACs()`\n    26→  - [ ] 1.4: Keep `getIntegrationRequiredACs()` as deprecated alias calling `getEnvironmentProvableACs()`\n    27→  - [ ] 1.5: Update the barrel export in `validation-acs.ts` to export both old and new names\n    28→- [ ] Task 2: Update `index.ts` re-exports (AC: 1, 2)\n    29→  - [ ] 2.1: Add `getTestProvableACs` and `getEnvironmentProvableACs` to the import/re-export in `src/modules/verify/index.ts`\n    30→  - [ ] 2.2: Keep old names in the export list (they're deprecated aliases, not removed)\n    31→- [ ] Task 3: Add mapping comment to `validation-runner.ts` (AC: 3)\n    32→  - [ ] 3.1: Add JSDoc above L106 (`if (ac.verificationMethod === 'integration')`) explaining the mapping: `'integration'` in `ValidationAC` corresponds to `environment-provable` in `VerificationTier`; `'cli'` corresponds to `test-provable`. No behavioral change.\n    33→- [ ] Task 4: Update comments in `validation-runner-types.ts` (AC: 4)\n    34→  - [ ] 4.1: Update L22 comment `'integration-required'` — add note that this is a status reason string, not a tier name; the corresponding tier is `environment-provable`\n    35→  - [ ] 4.2: Update L56 comment `blocked (integration-required or retry-exhausted)` to note tier correspondence\n    36→- [ ] Task 5: Add JSDoc to `VerificationMethod` type in `validation-ac-types.ts` (AC: 5)\n    37→  - [ ] 5.1: Add JSDoc to the `VerificationMethod` type alias explaining the correspondence to `VerificationTier`\n    38→\n    39→## Dev Notes\n    40→\n    41→This story is purely additive — rename functions, add deprecation aliases, update comments/JSDoc. No behavioral changes to any runtime logic.\n    42→\n    43→### Key Constraints\n    44→\n    45→- **Do NOT change `VerificationMethod` type values.** The `'cli' | 'integration'` values are used in the validation AC data arrays (`validation-ac-data.ts`) across 79 entries. Changing the type values would require updating all 79 data entries — that's out of scope. This story only adds vocabulary mapping comments.\n    46→- **Do NOT change the `'integration-required'` string** in `ValidationACResult.reason`. It's a status reason, not a tier name. Just add a comment noting the terminology difference.\n    47→- **Do NOT modify `validation-ac-data.ts`.** That file contains the 79 AC entries and is not in scope.\n    48→- **Keep all old function exports working.** Consumers use `getCliVerifiableACs()` and `getIntegrationRequiredACs()` — they must still work. The test file (`validation-acs.test.ts`) also imports them.\n    49→\n    50→### Consumers of renamed functions (must not break)\n    51→\n    52→1. `src/modules/verify/index.ts` L87-88: re-exports `getCliVerifiableACs`, `getIntegrationRequiredACs`\n    53→2. `src/modules/verify/__tests__/validation-acs.test.ts`: imports and tests both functions\n    54→3. `src/coverage/coverage-summary.json`: references function names (auto-generated, will update on next coverage run)\n    55→4. `src/modules/verify/AGENTS.md`: documents the functions\n    56→\n    57→### Current file state (from story 16-1, 16-2, 16-3)\n    58→\n    59→- `src/modules/verify/types.ts` already has `VerificationTier`, `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `maxTier()`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`\n    60→- `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` already uses `classifyTier()` with new tier vocabulary\n    61→- `src/modules/verify/proof.ts` already recognizes all four tier names in `**Tier:**` parsing\n    62→- `validation-acs.ts`, `validation-runner.ts`, `validation-runner-types.ts`, `validation-ac-types.ts` still use old vocabulary — this story updates them\n    63→\n    64→### Project Structure Notes\n    65→\n    66→- All files are in `src/modules/verify/` — the verify module\n    67→- Tests are in `src/modules/verify/__tests__/`\n    68→- NFR18: 300-line file limit. All target files are well under this limit.\n    69→- Follow existing JSDoc patterns: `/** @deprecated Use X instead. */`\n    70→\n    71→### References\n    72→\n    73→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/tech-spec-verification-tier-rework.md#Task 4] — \"Replace all cli-verifiable/integration-required references with new tier names\"\n    74→- [Source: src/modules/verify/types.ts#L10-L38] — `VerificationTier` type and `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` already defined\n    75→- [Source: src/modules/verify/validation-acs.ts#L34-L42] — Current function signatures to rename\n    76→- [Source: src/modules/verify/index.ts#L85-L89] — Re-exports that need updating\n    77→\n    78→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n    79→## Verification Requirements\n    80→\n    81→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-4-update-validation-acs-and-runner-proof.md)\n    82→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n    83→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n    84→\n    85→## Documentation Requirements\n    86→\n    87→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n    88→- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/16-4-update-validation-acs-and-runner.md\n    89→\n    90→## Testing Requirements\n    91→\n    92→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n    93→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n    94→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n    95→\n    96→## Dev Agent Record\n    97→\n    98→### Agent Model Used\n    99→\n   100→### Debug Log References\n   101→\n   102→### Completion Notes List\n   103→\n   104→### File List\n   105→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01LnSVSQepuckZac7ZtmSt3a","session_id":"15a05376-1038-4ca0-9130-3347fd423c16","uuid":"7ec89a1c-59dc-452d-9c0e-b89f59a6632e","timestamp":"2026-03-27T11:37:21.742Z"}
