n- `getEnvironmentProvableACs()` exists at `src/modules/verify/validation-acs.ts` L46-48\n- Filters `verificationMethod === 'integration'` (same data as old `getIntegrationRequiredACs()`)\n- `getIntegrationRequiredACs()` exists at L56-58 as deprecated alias calling `getEnvironmentProvableACs()`\n- JSDoc `@deprecated` tag present at L55\n- Both exported from `src/modules/verify/index.ts` L87-90\n- Tests exist: `describe('getEnvironmentProvableACs')` with 2 tests — all pass\n- Legacy test `'returns 24 environment-provable (integration) ACs'` — passes\n\n## AC3: executeValidationAC() JSDoc mapping comment for integration method\n\n**Result:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n- `src/modules/verify/validation-runner.ts` L106-111 contains JSDoc block:\n  ```\n  Tier mapping: `verificationMethod === 'integration'` in ValidationAC corresponds\n  to the `environment-provable` VerificationTier. Similarly, `'cli'` corresponds\n  to `test-provable`.\n  ```\n- No behavioral change — still returns `blocked` with reason `'integration-required'` (L118)\n- Function signature unchanged\n\n## AC4: validation-runner-types.ts comments updated with new tier names\n\n**Result:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n- `src/modules/verify/validation-runner-types.ts` L22-25 (reason field):\n  ```\n  Note: 'integration-required' is a status reason string, not a tier name.\n  The corresponding verification tier is `environment-provable`.\n  ```\n- L60-62 (blocked count):\n  ```\n  Note: 'integration-required' maps to the `environment-provable` verification tier;\n  'retry-exhausted' is a status reason unrelated to tier classification.\n  ```\n- `'integration-required'` string value kept unchanged (it's a status reason, not a tier name)\n\n## AC5: VerificationMethod type JSDoc with tier correspondence\n\n**Result:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n- `src/modules/verify/validation-ac-types.ts` L8-14 contains JSDoc:\n  ```\n  Correspondence to {@link VerificationTier} (from `types.ts`):\n  - `'cli'` maps to the `test-provable` tier — verifiable via CLI commands.\n  - `'integration'` maps to the `environment-provable` tier — requires a running integration environment.\n  ```\n- Type definition unchanged: `export type VerificationMethod = 'cli' | 'integration'` (L15)\n- Import of `VerificationTier` present at L6 for JSDoc reference\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Description | Result |\n|----|-------------|--------|\n| AC1 | getTestProvableACs + deprecated alias | PASS |\n| AC2 | getEnvironmentProvableACs + deprecated alias | PASS |\n| AC3 | executeValidationAC JSDoc mapping | PASS |\n| AC4 | validation-runner-types comments updated | PASS |\n| AC5 | VerificationMethod JSDoc correspondence | PASS |\n\n**Final Result: ALL_PASS (5/5 ACs)**\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":206,"cache_read_input_tokens":34678,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":206,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":51,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FoFHtsM2CKqpEhhndJ9EUV","session_id":"15a05376-1038-4ca0-9130-3347fd423c16","uuid":"de32d7ef-133e-44b2-8500-342c92e9e9bd"}
