{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0161tbfjxRquQE1AgXBqneHw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Verification Proof: Story 0.1 — Sprint Execution Skill\n     2→\n     3→**Verifier:** Claude Opus 4.6 (black-box)\n     4→**Date:** 2026-03-16\n     5→**Container:** codeharness-verify\n     6→**CLI Version:** codeharness 0.14.0\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## AC 1: Sprint-status.yaml parsing — finds current epic and next backlog story\n    11→\n    12→**Verified: PASS (partial — parsing logic confirmed, skill invocation blocked)**\n    13→\n    14→The `codeharness run` command reads sprint-status.yaml, parses `development_status`, and correctly identifies story counts by status.\n    15→\n    16→**Test 1: All backlog stories**\n    17→\n    18→```bash\n    19→docker exec -w /workspace codeharness-verify bash -c 'cat > _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml << \"SEOF\"\n    20→sprint: 1\n    21→development_status:\n    22→  epic-0: backlog\n    23→  0-1-sprint-execution-skill: backlog\n    24→  0-2-another-story: backlog\n    25→  epic-0-retrospective: optional\n    26→SEOF'\n    27→docker exec -w /workspace codeharness-verify codeharness run --json 2>&1 | head -1\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→```output\n    31→{\"status\":\"info\",\"message\":\"Starting autonomous execution — 2 ready, 0 in progress, 0 verified, 0/2 done\"}\n    32→```\n    33→\n    34→**Test 2: Mixed statuses — done, in-progress, backlog across two epics**\n    35→\n    36→```bash\n    37→docker exec -w /workspace codeharness-verify bash -c 'cat > _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml << \"SEOF\"\n    38→sprint: 1\n    39→development_status:\n    40→  epic-0: done\n    41→  0-1-sprint-execution-skill: done\n    42→  0-2-another-story: done\n    43→  epic-0-retrospective: done\n    44→  epic-1: backlog\n    45→  1-1-some-feature: done\n    46→  1-2-next-feature: in-progress\n    47→  1-3-last-feature: backlog\n    48→