{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016uvg8M8B7cku9a1pm6NwnC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — create-story (2026-03-27T11:02Z)\n     4→\n     5→Story file already existed. Updated verification tags from `test-provable` to `cli-verifiable` format.\n     6→\n     7→## Token Report\n     8→- Total tool calls: 10\n     9→- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 5, Edit: 1, Glob: 3\n    10→- Files read: 5 unique, 5 total reads\n    11→\n    12→### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — dev (2026-03-27T11:05Z)\n    13→\n    14→No issues reported. Clean implementation — 2 files changed, 9 new tests added.\n    15→\n    16→## Token Report\n    17→- Total tool calls: 12\n    18→- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 5, Glob: 2, Grep: 1, Bash: 2\n    19→- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads\n    20→\n    21→### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — code-review (2026-03-27T11:09Z)\n    22→\n    23→**Bugs found:**\n    24→- HIGH: Metrics zeroed when Docker enforcement skipped — downstream consumers see false zeroes. Fixed.\n    25→- HIGH: `black-box` missing from LEGACY_TIER_MAP. Fixed.\n    26→- MEDIUM: Hardcoded tier names in regex (not derived from types.ts). Fixed with dynamic regex.\n    27→- MEDIUM: No test for unrecognized tier value. Fixed.\n    28→\n    29→## Token Report\n    30→- Total tool calls: 21\n    31→- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 6, Edit: 5, Grep: 5, Glob: 4, Skill: 1\n    32→\n    33→### 16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers — verify (2026-03-27T11:24Z)\n    34→\n    35→ALL_PASS (6/6 ACs). Unit-testable tier — no Docker needed. Build, tests (3887 pass), coverage 96.86%.\n    36→\n    37→## Token Report\n    38→- Total tool calls: 13\n    39→- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 3, Grep: 2, Write: 1\n    40→\n    41→### State corruption fix (2026-03-27T11:00Z)\n    42→\n    43→sprint-state.json had 4 stories (14-5, 14-6, 16-1, 16-2) reverted from `done` to `review` despite commits confirming them as done. Proof documents existed. Fixed by restoring `done` status. Root cause: likely ralph state reconciliation overwriting committed state between sessions.\n    44→\n    45→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verify (2026-03-27T08:20Z)\n    46→\n    47→Tier A validation — proof existed with 10/10 PASS. Quick validation pass.\n    48→\n    49→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — review (2026-03-27T08:25Z)\n    50→\n    51→**Bugs found:**\n    52→- HIGH: Unsafe `as StackName` type cast in `dockerfile-generator.ts` masking type safety — FIXED\n    53→- MEDIUM: Double `apt-get update` layer in Rust+Bevy Dockerfile output — FIXED\n    54→- MEDIUM: Unquoted Python dist filename in COPY instruction (`env.ts:162`) — NOT FIXED\n    55→\n    56→**Tech debt:**\n    57→- 14 stale `mockDetectStack` call sites in `verify-env.test.ts`\n    58→- No logging when `getStackProvider()` returns undefined\n    59→\n    60→## Token Report\n    61→- Total tool calls: 20\n    62→- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 3, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n    63→- Files read: 13 unique, 14 total reads\n    64→\n    65→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — code-review (2026-03-27T09:35Z)\n    66→\n    67→**Bugs found and fixed:**\n    68→- HIGH: Subdirectory stack path not resolved before passing to provider — Bevy detection would silently fail for non-root stacks\n    69→- MEDIUM: Missing DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive — apt installs could hang on interactive prompts\n    70→- MEDIUM: Uncovered !provider and !section branches (66.66% branch coverage before fix)\n    71→- MEDIUM: env.ts at 305 lines (extra blank line), over NFR1 300-line limit\n    72→\n    73→**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n    74→- verify-env.test.ts still mocks dead detectStack import\n    75→- Multi-stack Dockerfile creates redundant apt-get update per provider section\n    76→- env.ts at 304 lines still over 300-line NFR1 limit\n    77→- Story Dev Agent Record claims 